ost extraordinary palaces by hand]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132535525.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/in-1879-a-french-postman-picked-up-a-strange-stone-over-the-next-33-years-he-built-one-of-europes-most-extraordinary-palaces-by-hand/articleshow/132535525.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/in-1879-a-french-postman-picked-up-a-strange-stone-over-the-next-33-years-he-built-one-of-europes-most-extraordinary-palaces-by-hand/articleshow/132535525.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-21T17:10:18+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132535688,imgsize-242311.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Scientists deploy robot birds in Wyoming's Grand Teton National Park to lure a critically declining local sage-grouse population away from an airport and revive its numbers]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132534016.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/scientists-deploy-robot-birds-in-wyomings-grand-teton-national-park-to-lure-a-critically-declining-local-sage-grouse-population-away-from-an-airport-and-revive-its-numbers/articleshow/132534016.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/scientists-deploy-robot-birds-in-wyomings-grand-teton-national-park-to-lure-a-critically-declining-local-sage-grouse-population-away-from-an-airport-and-revive-its-numbers/articleshow/132534016.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-21T16:25:27+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132534454,imgsize-1553600.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Mosquito spraying backfires as 84% develop resistance in US neighbourhoods]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132534007.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[New research indicates mosquito spraying is causing insect resistance.  Genetic markers for resistance are now widespread across many residential blocks.  This resistance is more prevalent in wealthier neighborhoods where spraying occurs frequently.  Overuse of chemicals is making insecticides less effective over time.  Integrated pest management offers a more sustainable solution for mosquito control.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/us-and-world/wealthy-us-neighbourhoods-paid-to-spray-mosquitoes-by-2023-the-insects-had-evolved-resistance-across-84-of-sampled-blocks-and-know-what-they-became-capable-of/articleshow/132534007.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/us-and-world/wealthy-us-neighbourhoods-paid-to-spray-mosquitoes-by-2023-the-insects-had-evolved-resistance-across-84-of-sampled-blocks-and-know-what-they-became-capable-of/articleshow/132534007.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-21T16:11:04+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132534089,imgsize-67376.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Middle East crisis, South China Sea tensions dominate ASEAN top diplomats meetings]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132533571.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/middle-east-crisis-south-china-sea-tensions-dom